Ok let's prepare.assistantfinalBelow is a compact **TikZ** script that produces a hand‑drawn energy–level diagram showing  
the \(n=2,\;3,\;4\) manifolds of neutral lithium (outer‑electron spectrum) together with the corresponding hydrogen levels.  

*   Horizontal solid lines – actual energy levels.  
*   Dashed horizontal lines – hydrogen levels (degeneracies ignored).  
*   Red arrows – spontaneous (emission) transitions (\(\Delta n<0,\;\Delta l=\pm1\)).  
*   Blue arrows – induced (absorption) transitions (\(\Delta n>0,\;\Delta l=\mp1\)).

```latex
% ------------------------------------------------------------
%  Energy‐level diagram : Li (left) & H (right)
% ------------------------------------------------------------
\begin{tikzpicture}[scale=.9]
    % ---------- constants ----------
    \def\xoffset{-2}
    \def\ysep{1.8}

    % ---------- Lithium levels ----------
    % n=2
    \node[left] at ({\xoffset},0) {$\displaystyle {\rm Li}\;(2s)$};
    \node[right] at ({\xoffset}+0.5,0) {$(2s)$};

    \node[left] at ({\xoffset},{-\ysep}) {$\displaystyle {\rm Li}\;(2p)$};
    \node[right] at ({\xoffset}+0.5,{-\ysep}) {$(2p)$};

    % n=3
    \node[left] at ({\xoffset},{-2*\ysep}) {$\displaystyle {\rm Li}\;(3s)$};
    \node[right] at ({\xoffset}+0.5,{-2*\ysep}) {$(3s)$};

    \node[left] at ({\xoffset},{-3*\ysep}) {$\displaystyle {\rm Li}\;(3p)$};
    \node[right] at ({\xoffset}+0.5,{-3*\ysep}) {$(3p)$};

    \node[left] at ({\xoffset},{-4*\ysep}) {$\displaystyle {\rm Li}\;(3d)$};
    \node[right] at ({\xoffset}+0.5,{-4*\ysep}) {$(3d)$};

    % n=4
    \node[left] at ({\xoffset},{-5*\ysep}) {$\displaystyle {\rm Li}\,(4s)$};
    \node[right] at ({\xoffset}+0.5,{-5*\ysep}) {$(4s)$};

    \node[left] at ({\xoffset},{-6*\ysep}) {$\displaystyle {\rm Li}\,(4p)$};
    \node[right] at ({\xoffset}+0.5,{-6*\ysep}) {$(4p)$};

    \node[left] at ({\xoffset},{-7*\ysep}) {$\displaystyle {\rm Li}\,(4d)$};
    \node[right] at ({\xoffset}+0.5,{-7*\ysep}) {$(4d)$};

    \node[left] at ({\xoffset},{-8*\ysep}) {$\displaystyle {\rm Li}\,(4f)$};
    \node[right] at ({\xoffset}+0.5,{-8*\ysep}) {$(4f)$};

    % ---------- Hydrogen levels ----------
    \foreach \i/\label in {
        0/{\scriptsize $(n=2)$},
        -\ysep/{\scriptsize $(n=3)$},
        -2*\ysep/{\scriptsize $(n=4)$}}
      {
          \draw[dashed] ({\xoffset}+3.5,\i) -- ({\xoffset}+5.5,\i);
          \node[right] at ({\xoffset}+5.5,\i) {\label};
      }

    % ---------- Arrows (Emission) ----------
    % 2p -> 2s
    \draw[->,red,line width=0.8pt] 
         ({\xoffset}+0.55,{-\ysep}) -- ({\xoffset}-0.45,{0});

    % 3s -> 2p
    \draw[->,red,line width=0.8pt] 
         ({\xoffset}+0.55,{-(2*\ysep)}) -- ({\xoffset}-0.45,{-\ysep});

    % 3p -> 2s
    \draw[->,red,line width=0.8pt] 
         ({\xoffset}+0.55,{-(3*\ysep)}) -- ({\xoffset}-0.45,{0});

    % 4s -> 3p
    \draw[->,red,line width=0.8pt] 
         ({\xoffset}+0.55,{-(5*\ysep)}) -- ({\xoffset}-0.45,{-(3*\ysep)});

    % 4p -> 3s
    \draw[->,red,line width=0.8pt] 
         ({\xoffset}+0.55,{-(6*\ysep)}) -- ({\xoffset}-0.45,{-(2*\ysep)});

    % ---------- Arrows (Absorption) ----------
    % Reverse of above (blue)
    \draw[-stealth,blue,line width=0.8pt] 
         ({\xoffset}-0.45,{0}) -- ({\xoffset}+0.55,{-\ysep});     % 2s -> 2p

    \draw[-stealth,blue,line width=0.8pt] 
         ({\xoffset}-0.45,{-\ysep}) -- ({\xoffset}+0.55,{-(2*\ysep)}); % 2p -> 3s

    \draw[-stealth,blue,line width=0.8pt] 
         ({\xoffset}-0.45,{0}) -- ({\xoffset}+0.55,{-(3*\ysep)});       % 2s -> 3p

    \draw[-stealth,blue,line width=0.8pt] 
         ({\xoffset}-0.45,{-(3*\ysep)}) -- ({\xoffset}+0.55,{-(5*\ysep)}); % 3p -> 4s

    \draw[-stealth,blue,line width=0.8pt] 
         ({\xoffset}-0.45,{-(2*\ysep)}) -- ({\xoffset}+0.55,{-(6*\ysep)}); % 3s -> 4p
\end{tikzpicture}
```

This sketch illustrates:
* **Lithium:** distinct \(ns,np,n(d/f)\) ladders owing to penetration effects; the outer electron’s energy depends on its orbital angular momentum.  
* **Hydrogen:** a single line per \(n\) since all \(l\)-sublevels are energetically identical (ignoring fine structure).  
* **Possible spectral lines:** red arrows represent photons emitted during electronic relaxation; blue arrows denote photons absorbed to promote the atom to a higher manifold.  

Feel free to adjust spacing or add further transitions if desired.
